The goal of this PR is to remove the JS stubs that are hard-coded into the Javascript loader because large applications can potentially generate a large amount of these stubs.

The idea here is to generate them dynamically using a proxy handler for the main module. However, there is a bug now whereby minified imports and exports between Javascript and Wasm are not honoured because the names of missing functions are removed from the Javascript loader.

